text: Edmund March Blunt (born on June 20, 1770) was a ship navigator and he also was a publisher. He created a magazine called American Coastal Pilot. He was born in Portsmouth, New Hampshire. He also lived in Ossining, New York. He had three sons. ==References== Category:1770 births Category:Year of death unknown Category:American explorers Category:People from Portsmouth, New Hampshire
title: Edmund March Blunt
